description: Borrowed from Dharug gunya (“shelter”), first recorded 1803.

entries.meaning: (Australia) A traditional Aboriginal dwelling made of bark and sticks.
examples: The following day we reached the main creek ; and knowing where there was a fine water-hole and native gunyahs, we went there, intending to save what was left of our flour and dried meat, for the purpose of making another attempt to reach Mount Hopeless.
